metadata.name: Finding Light In Darkness
metadata.description:
Thoughts 
Within us all
Often clouded
Sometimes clear
In this moment 
There was nothing
Not even fear
What will tomorrow bring?

We all have fears. From an early age I would hate being out at night on my own. The thought that something would happen would always enter my head. Sadly itâ€™s still something that bothers me to this day. I recently wanted to start photographing more at night but honestly the anxiety would sometimes be too much. I would put it off all the time until I finally found the courage to get out there. Often, there are amazing things on the other side of fear, and on that night, there was.
